    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-03-02T19:34:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-03-02T19:34:00-05:00" n="522"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d522">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.77/1976: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Acting President of the Technical Board</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Harbin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-03-03T09:00:00+08:26">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 3, 1921—9 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received March 3—8:27 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Far Eastern Republic is about to request Railway Committee that the activities
                    Railway Committee and Technical Board be extended to include all Far Eastern
                    Republic railways. What attitude does the Department desire us to assume?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
